<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=heimdall00>Heimdall00</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#333333>(1/26/03 11:59:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=346.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Soloing The Grey questions</span><hr size=1> Very easy to solo Grey even at 55, but exp is not even close to dryads, not to mention lack of loot. If you want, you can setup next to zone from ML, and pull the golems, they have minimal health and go down fast with you just dropping 1-2 nukes (I used SoS exclusively, since I am conj spec). The only mobs that drop any kind of loot are nameds that are spawned by running over &quot;traps&quot; that are all over the desert, usually on top of protruding rocks. Be careful, as they also spawn shimmering rockfiends that are immune to spells and will tear you apart. Not worth it in my opinion.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jochangaladar>Jochan Galadar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 881<br> <font color=#333333>(1/27/03 4:26:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=346.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Soloing The Grey questions</span><hr size=1> I did all of 57, 58, and most of 59 in the Grey.<br>
<br>
Chaining is the most efficient approach.  Yes, I have done the Mons Wall camp, pulling wanderers to the safe part of the wall.<br>
<br>
Shimmering Rockfiends have minimal resistance vs. Magic, and major resistance vs. Cold and Fire.  They also have about 10,000 hit points.  In addition, they have a very large assist/aggro radius and on occasion see invis.  They are flagged as Summoned, so Anti-Summoned-type nukes work on them, as well as Banishment.<br>
<br>
The cash drops in the Grey are generally minimal, but livable.  It can certainly keep you stocked up on Cat's Eye Agate and Malachite. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jeffsterinsf>jeffsterinsf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#333333>(3/6/03 5:44:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=346.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Where are the Organs?</span><hr size=1> The Grey camp at the ML zone-in seems very nice at 56, non-epic. XP isn't too bad and reasonably safe with the zone-line nearby. Thanks for the pointer on Shimmering Rockfiends being summoned -- they are a PAIN -- yes, HUGE aggro range.<br>
<br>
Another warning is that the golems have a *nasty* spin-you-around stun, so if you are chaining, don't fizzle!<br>
<br>
Looking to complete the Amulet quest, but haven't gotten any organs off the snakes that roam by. Are the organs off snakes in a different area? EB stones work just fine, but would occasionally like to drop something permanent on if I need to go AFK for more than a couple minutes. Also, any casters in the zone likely to dispell EB?<br>
<br>
Itchy <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm24.showPrevMessage?topicID=346.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm24.showNextMessage?topicID=346.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=346.topic&index=3><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm24.threadControl?topicID=346.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/unread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm24.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=346.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm24.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=346.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub102.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="themagicianstowerannouncements">Administration<option value="themagicianstowergeneral">General<option value="themagicianstowerfrm32">Class Balance<option value="themagicianstowerfrm45">User Interface<option value="themagicianstowerspells">Spells<option value="themagicianstowerequipmentandquests">Quests<option value="themagicianstowerfrm28">Equipment<option value="themagicianstowerfrm29">Magician Pets<option value="themagicianstowerfrm30">Magician Skills<o